Today I read a research paper about detecting whether a piece of text is written by a human or generated by AI.
The study compared traditional machine learning models like XGBoost and Random Forest with modern NLP models like RoBERTa and T5-Sentinel.
I found it interesting that the traditional models performed almost as well as the advanced AI models.
The researchers also used LIME to explain which words influenced the model's decisions, making the predictions easier to understand.
This shows that simple and efficient models can still be very useful when combined with explainable AI, especially in areas like education and media.

Paper: HULLMI: Human vs. LLM Identification with Explainability (2025)

Link:https://arxiv.org/abs/2409.04808
